@bluebill1049, Okay that fixed the first issue (deleting field array in watch). Awesome!

There is still an issue with `reset(values)` - it seems to cause an error when you delete an item from the field array and then submit the form.

![Screen Shot 2020-04-13 at 9 08 49 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10138447/79175214-1907dc00-7dcb-11ea-93f6-43de44b643f1.png)

Notice 3 is due to 

```
const onSubmit = values => {
    console.log(
      "%c submit clicked",
      "background: #ec5990; color: white; display: block;"
    );
    console.log("onSubmit Values", values);
    reset(values); // this line
  };
```

in side react hook form we do invoke native HTML reset, which leads the form to be empty value and hence defaultValues gets print out from `watch()`;
